r the broad ocean area north of Wake Island from a U.S. Air Force C-17 aircraft, staged from Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam, Hawaii. The AN/TPY-2 X-band radar, located with the THAAD system on Meck Island, tracked the E-LRALT and a THAAD interceptor successfully intercepted the Medium-Range Ballistic Missile. THAAD was operated by Soldiers from the 32nd AAMDC.\r\n\r\nAnother short-range ballistic missile was launched from a mobile launch platform located in the broad ocean area northeast of Kwajalein Atoll. The PATRIOT system, manned by soldiers of the 94th AAMDC, detected, tracked and successfully intercepted the target with a PAC-3 interceptor.\r\n\r\nThe USS FITZGERALD successfully engaged a low flying cruise missile over water.\r\n\r\nThe Aegis system also tracked and launched an SM-3 Block 1A interceptor against a Short-Range Ballistic Missile. However, despite indication of a nominal flight of the SM-3 Block 1A interceptor, there was no indication of an intercept of the SRBM.\r\n\r\nFTI-01 was a combined developmental and operational test. Soldiers, Sailors, and Airmen from multiple Combatant Commands operated the systems and were provided a unique opportunity to refine operational doctrine and tactics. Program officials continue to assess and evaluate system performance based upon telemetry and other data obtained during the test.','Complex Missile Defense Test','','publish','open','open','','auto-draft-18','','','2017-03-22 04:05:01','2017-03-22 04:05:01','',0,'http://54.172.133.99/komandov3/watch/1639/auto-draft-18',3,'post','',0),(1640,1,'2017-03-22 04:04:37','2017-03-22 04:04:37','Komputer Kindergarten / Madeleine, January 2014<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is a character based on radio/tv personality Kim Komando who teaches us how to use computers and how to live life.','First Life workshop - \"does it blow up?\"','','publish','closed','closed','','auto-draft-24','','','2017-03-22 04:06:03','2017-03-22 04:06:03','',0,'http://54.172.133.99/komandov3/watch/video